data.description: Escape to this beautifully remodeled 1930 mountain home in Valle Crucis, just two miles from the historic Mast General Store. Multiple outdoor gathering areas, hot tub, outdoor fireplace and fire pit, barn and outbuilding would make this an ideal property for Airbnb or Vrbo. This four-bedroom, 3.5 bath home includes a one-bedroom, one-bath furnished studio apartment. Studio apartment has a full kitchen, living and dining area, full bedroom & bath, and a 24'x24' private deck. Current rent is $750 a month. On 0.87 acres, home features massive, exposed beams and soaring wood-burning fireplace in the family room, gourmet kitchen with walk-in pantry, two primary bedrooms with en suites with heated floors in each bath, two additional bedrooms with Jack and Jill bath, two-car garage and plenty of storage in the unfinished basement. Bring the whole family and friends to enjoy the charm of Valle Crucis and all High Country has to offer.
